str2: Enoch, son of Jared and father of Methuselah. Of Hebrew origin; Enoch, an antediluvian.
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.
Adam, the first man, the first parent of the human race. Of Hebrew origin; Adam, the first man; typically man.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: From prophetes; to foretell events, divine, speak under inspiration, exercise the prophetic office.

parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: See! Lo! Behold! Look! Second person singular imperative middle voice of eido; used as imperative lo!
Lord, master, sir; the Lord. From kuros; supreme in authority, i.e. controller; by implication, Master.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular

str2: In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
A myriad, group of ten thousand, a ten thousand. From murioi; a ten-thousand; by extension, a 'myriad' or indefinite number.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
Set apart by (or for) God, holy, sacred. From hagos; sacred.
